Overly concise Matlab version. If you get Dan Ellis&#x27; ispecgram [1] you can do something like:<p><pre><code>    [x, sr] = wavread(&#x27;rick.wav&#x27;);
    x_mono = mean(x,2);
    X = specgram(x_mono, nfft, sr);
    Y = X >= imdilate(X, ones(mask_size), &#x27;same&#x27;);
    y = ispecgram(Y, nfft, sr);
    % wavwrite(y, sr, &#x27;roll.wav&#x27;);
</code></pre>
params: nfft, masksize (tuple)<p>[1] <a href="http://github.com/tbertinmahieux/MSongsDB/blob/master/MatlabSrc/ispecgram.m" rel="nofollow">http://github.com/tbertinmahieux/MSongsDB/blob/master/Matlab...</a>
